p: Histopathological analysis from the hind paw of MAYV/IRES-vaccinated mice revealed maintenance of tissue architecture, in contrast to the disruption caused by WT MAYV injection (Fig. 5k). ELISA analysis from the spleen of vaccinated mice revealed a reduction in levels of the cytokines IL-1β (Fig. 6a), IL-6 (Fig. 6b), IFN-γ (Fig. 6c) and TNF-α (Fig. 6d) as well as the chemokines, CCL2 (Fig. 6e), CCL3 (Fig. 6F), CCL4 (Fig. 6g) and CCL5 (Fig. 6h).
